    'intermediate',
    10,
    'Explore pros and cons of both changing and staying the same; Give equal attention to both sides of ambivalence; Avoid using decisional balance to persuade; Let the colleague draw their own conclusions',
    'A colleague is ambivalent about applying for a promotion. Practice exploring both sides of the decision balance.',
    '{"name": "James", "role": "colleague", "background": "Team member considering promotion to team lead but ambivalent. Weighing pros and cons.", "personality_traits": ["ambivalent", "thoughtful", "cautious", "analytical"], "tone_spectrum": {"word_complexity": 0.4, "sentence_length": 0.4, "emotional_expressiveness": 0.4, "disclosure_level": 0.3, "response_latency": 0.5, "confidence_level": 0.4}, "starting_tone_position": 0.4, "triggers": ["pressure", "being told what to do", "dismissiveness"], "comfort_topics": ["autonomy", "understanding", "options", "support"]}'::jsonb,
    '{"start_node_id": "dec_1", "nodes": {"dec_1": {"id": "dec_1", "persona_text": "I know the team lead position is open, and I''ve been encouraged to apply. But I''m honestly not sure if I want it. I go back and forth.", "persona_mood": "neutral_uncertain", "themes": ["Ambivalence", "Goals", "Change"], "choice_points": [{"id": "cp_dec_1_0", "option_text": "The promotion would be great for your career. You should definitely go for it.", "preview_hint": "Persuasive approach", "rapport_impact": 0, "resistance_impact": 0, "tone_shift": 0.0, "technique_tags": ["unknown"], "competency_links": [], "feedback": {"immediate": "This tries to argue them out of ambivalence rather than exploring it.", "learning_note": "Ambivalence is normal in change - our role is to explore it, not resolve it."}, "next_node_id": "dec_2a", "exploration_depth": "surface"}, {"id": "cp_dec_1_1", "option_text": "You''re feeling torn about this. What are some of the good things about staying in your current role?", "preview_hint": "MI-consistent approach", "rapport_impact": 1, "resistance_impact": -1, "tone_shift": 0.15, "technique_tags": ["open_question", "decisional_balance"], "competency_links": ["B6"], "feedback": {"immediate": "Excellent - acknowledges ambivalence and starts by exploring one side openly.", "learning_note": "Ambivalence is normal in change - our role is to explore it, not resolve it."}, "next_node_id": "dec_2b", "exploration_depth": "surface"}, {"id": "cp_dec_1_2", "option_text": "You''re just being indecisive. You need to make up your mind.", "preview_hint": "MI-consistent approach", "rapport_impact": 0, "resistance_impact": 0, "tone_shift": 0.0, "technique_tags": ["unknown"], "competency_links": [], "feedback": {"immediate": "This treats normal ambivalence as a character flaw, damaging the relationship.", "learning_note": "Ambivalence is normal in change - our role is to explore it, not resolve it."}, "next_node_id": "dec_2a", "exploration_depth": "surface"}], "is_endpoint": false, "endpoint_type": null}, "dec_2a": {"id": "dec_2a", "persona_text": "It''s not that simple. I have a lot to consider here. This is my career we''re talking about.", "persona_mood": "neutral_uncertain", "themes": ["General"], "choice_points": [{"id": "cp_dec_2a_0", "option_text": "You need to prioritize your career growth. Staying put will hold you back.", "preview_hint": "MI-consistent approach", "rapport_impact": 0, "resistance_impact": 0, "tone_shift": 0.0, "technique_tags": ["unknown"], "competency_links": [], "feedback": {"immediate": "This continues the argumentative dynamic and increases resistance.", "learning_note": "Watch for colleague resistance signals - defensiveness or disengagement."}, "next_node_id": "dec_end_poor", "exploration_depth": "surface"}, {"id": "cp_dec_2a_1", "option_text": "You''re right, this is an important decision that deserves careful consideration. What matters to you in making this choice?", "preview_hint": "MI-consistent approach", "rapport_impact": 0, "resistance_impact": 0, "tone_shift": 0.0, "technique_tags": ["unknown"], "competency_links": [], "feedback": {"immediate": "Good recovery - validates the importance and invites exploration.", "learning_note": "Continue practicing MI techniques to build your coaching skills."}, "next_node_id": "dec_3a", "exploration_depth": "surface"}], "is_endpoint": false, "endpoint_type": null}, "dec_2b": {"id": "dec_2b", "persona_text": "Well, I really enjoy the work I do now. I''m good at it, I have great relationships with my customers, and I can leave work at work without thinking about it constantly. Plus, I have time for my family and hobbies.", "persona_mood": "neutral_uncertain", "themes": ["Goals", "Motivation"], "choice_points": [{"id": "cp_dec_2b_0", "option_text": "Those things aren''t as important as career advancement. You need to think about your future.", "preview_hint": "MI-consistent approach", "rapport_impact": 0, "resistance_impact": 0, "tone_shift": 0.0, "technique_tags": ["unknown"], "competency_links": [], "feedback": {"immediate": "This devalues what matters to them, creating discord.", "learning_note": "Continue practicing MI techniques to build your coaching skills."}, "next_node_id": "dec_2a", "exploration_depth": "surface"}, {"id": "cp_dec_2b_1", "option_text": "You enjoy your current work, you''re good at it, you have good customer relationships, and it allows you work-life balance with time for family and hobbies. Those are real benefits. And what, if anything, concerns you about staying where you are?", "preview_hint": "MI-consistent approach", "rapport_impact": 1, "resistance_impact": -1, "tone_shift": 0.15, "technique_tags": ["reflection", "decisional_balance"], "competency_links": ["B6"], "feedback": {"immediate": "Perfect - gives equal weight to both sides without judgment.", "learning_note": "Continue practicing MI techniques to build your coaching skills."}, "next_node_id": "dec_3b", "exploration_depth": "surface"}], "is_endpoint": false, "endpoint_type": null}, "dec_3a": {"id": "dec_3a", "persona_text": "I want to make the right choice. I don''t want to regret this either way.", "persona_mood": "neutral_uncertain", "themes": ["Goals"], "choice_points": [{"id": "cp_dec_3a_0", "option_text": "Making the right choice matters to you. Let''s explore both options so you can feel confident in whatever you decide.", "preview_hint": "MI-consistent approach", "rapport_impact": 0, "resistance_impact": 0, "tone_shift": 0.0, "technique_tags": ["unknown"], "competency_links": [], "feedback": {"immediate": "Good - acknowledges their concern and offers balanced exploration.", "learning_note": "Continue practicing MI techniques to build your coaching skills."}, "next_node_id": "dec_3b", "exploration_depth": "surface"}, {"id": "cp_dec_3a_1", "option_text": "Well, you can''t predict the future. Just pick one.", "preview_hint": "MI-consistent approach", "rapport_impact": 0, "resistance_impact": 0, "tone_shift": 0.0, "technique_tags": ["unknown"], "competency_links": [], "feedback": {"immediate": "This dismisses their concern and pressures for a decision.", "learning_note": "Continue practicing MI techniques to build your coaching skills."}, "next_node_id": "dec_end_poor", "exploration_depth": "surface"}], "is_endpoint": false, "endpoint_type": null}, "dec_3b": {"id": "dec_3b", "persona_text": "I guess I worry about stagnating. If I stay in my current role, will I still be growing? And the salary increase would be nice. But then, what if I fail as a lead? What if I''m miserable?", "persona_mood": "neutral_uncertain", "themes": ["Goals", "Barriers", "Change"], "choice_points": [{"id": "cp_dec_3b_0", "option_text": "Exactly! So clearly you need to take the promotion. The growth and salary are worth it.", "preview_hint": "MI-consistent approach", "rapport_impact": 0, "resistance_impact": 0, "tone_shift": 0.0, "technique_tags": ["unknown"], "competency_links": [], "feedback": {"immediate": "This tries to use their concerns to argue rather than continuing balanced exploration.", "learning_note": "Continue practicing MI techniques to build your coaching skills."}, "next_node_id": "dec_2a", "exploration_depth": "surface"}, {"id": "cp_dec_3b_1", "option_text": "So you have growth and financial reasons to consider the promotion, but also real concerns about whether you''d succeed and enjoy it. What else might be benefits of taking the lead role?", "preview_hint": "MI-consistent approach", "rapport_impact": 1, "resistance_impact": -1, "tone_shift": 0.15, "technique_tags": ["reflection", "open_question"], "competency_links": ["B6"], "feedback": {"immediate": "Good - acknowledges concerns and explores potential change benefits.", "learning_note": "Continue practicing MI techniques to build your coaching skills."}, "next_node_id": "dec_4a", "exploration_depth": "surface"}], "is_endpoint": false, "endpoint_type": null}, "dec_4a": {"id": "dec_4a", "persona_text": "I could help shape the team. I have ideas about how we could improve things. And I''d be developing leadership skills, which could open more doors later.", "persona_mood": "neutral_uncertain", "themes": ["Motivation", "Change"], "choice_points": [{"id": "cp_dec_4a_0", "option_text": "So there are benefits on both sides - the work-life balance and enjoyment of your current role, versus growth, leadership development, and ability to shape the team. What concerns you about staying where you are?", "preview_hint": "MI-consistent approach", "rapport_impact": 1, "resistance_impact": -1, "tone_shift": 0.15, "technique_tags": ["complex_reflection", "open_question"], "competency_links": ["B6"], "feedback": {"immediate": "Excellent - summarizes both sides and explores costs of status quo.", "learning_note": "Continue practicing MI techniques to build your coaching skills."}, "next_node_id": "dec_5a", "exploration_depth": "surface"}, {"id": "cp_dec_4a_1", "option_text": "Those are great reasons. You should definitely apply.", "preview_hint": "MI-consistent approach", "rapport_impact": 0, "resistance_impact": 0, "tone_shift": 0.0, "technique_tags": ["unknown"], "competency_links": [], "feedback": {"immediate": "This moves to persuasion rather than continuing balanced exploration.", "learning_note": "Continue practicing MI techniques to build your coaching skills."}, "next_node_id": "dec_2a", "exploration_depth": "surface"}], "is_endpoint": false, "endpoint_type": null}, "dec_5a": {"id": "dec_5a", "persona_text": "I think about whether I''ll regret not trying. Will I look back in 5 years and wonder ''what if?'' That scares me more than failing, honestly.", "persona_mood": "neutral_uncertain", "themes": ["Goals", "Change"], "choice_points": [{"id": "cp_dec_5a_0", "option_text": "So on one side you have stability and work-life balance, on the other you have growth, leadership development, shaping the team, and avoiding future regret. Where does all this leave you?", "preview_hint": "MI-consistent approach", "rapport_impact": 1, "resistance_impact": -1, "tone_shift": 0.15, "technique_tags": ["summary_reflection", "open_question"], "competency_links": ["B6"], "feedback": {"immediate": "Perfect - gives equal weight to both sides and lets colleague draw conclusions.", "learning_note": "Continue practicing MI techniques to build your coaching skills."}, "next_node_id": "dec_6a", "exploration_depth": "surface"}, {"id": "cp_dec_5a_1", "option_text": "That''s a good point. So you should apply then.", "preview_hint": "MI-consistent approach", "rapport_impact": 0, "resistance_impact": 0, "tone_shift": 0.0, "technique_tags": ["unknown"], "competency_links": [], "feedback": {"immediate": "This takes over rather than letting them work through the ambivalence.", "learning_note": "Ambivalence is normal in change - our role is to explore it, not resolve it."}, "next_node_id": "dec_2a", "exploration_depth": "surface"}], "is_endpoint": false, "endpoint_type": null}, "dec_6a": {"id": "dec_6a", "persona_text": "I guess... I''m realizing that both options have real merit. Maybe I could talk to the current team lead about what the role is really like day-to-day? That might help me decide.", "persona_mood": "neutral_uncertain", "themes": ["Ambivalence", "Change"], "choice_points": [{"id": "cp_dec_6a_0", "option_text": "That''s a thoughtful next step - gathering more information to help with the decision. What would you want to learn from that conversation?", "preview_hint": "MI-consistent approach", "rapport_impact": 1, "resistance_impact": -1, "tone_shift": 0.15, "technique_tags": ["affirmation", "open_question"], "competency_links": ["A6"], "feedback": {"immediate": "Excellent - affirms their approach and invites exploration of what would help.", "learning_note": "Continue practicing MI techniques to build your coaching skills."}, "next_node_id": "dec_end_good", "exploration_depth": "surface"}, {"id": "cp_dec_6a_1", "option_text": "Sure, but honestly you should just apply. You''re clearly qualified.", "preview_hint": "MI-consistent approach", "rapport_impact": 0, "resistance_impact": 0, "tone_shift": 0.0, "technique_tags": ["unknown"], "competency_links": [], "feedback": {"immediate": "This takes over the decision-making instead of letting them explore.", "learning_note": "Continue practicing MI techniques to build your coaching skills."}, "next_node_id": "dec_end_poor", "exploration_depth": "surface"}], "is_endpoint": false, "endpoint_type": null}, "dec_end_good": {"id": "dec_end_good", "persona_text": "I want to understand the time commitment and how much of the role is people management vs technical work. Also, what support is available for new leads. Having that information would help me weigh things better.", "persona_mood": "neutral_uncertain", "themes": ["Autonomy", "Change"], "choice_points": [], "is_endpoint": true, "endpoint_type": "neutral_end"}, "dec_end_poor": {"id": "dec_end_poor", "persona_text": "I don''t think you understand what I''m wrestling with. I''ll figure it out on my own.", "persona_mood": "neutral_uncertain", "themes": ["General"], "choice_points": [], "is_endpoint": true, "endpoint_type": "failed_engagement"}}}'::jsonb,
